OL,3,CMan reunited with father's wartime
OL,4,Cdocuments found hidden in desk drawer
OL,6,FMr Reid discovered the papers had
OL,7,Fbelonged to the late Ian Rodger, from
OL,8,FGlasgow, who served with 2 Squadron of
OL,9,Fthe 6th Armoured Division Signal
OL,10,FRegiment, a unit of the British Army,
OL,11,Fand fought in Italy and Tunisia during
OL,12,Fthe war.
OL,14,FAfter hearing about the discovery
OL,15,Ffollowing an appeal for information
OL,16,Fmade through the Church of Scotland,
OL,17,FMr Rodger's son Sandy came forward to
OL,18,Fclaim the documents.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
