OL,3,CMan reunited with father's wartime
OL,4,Cdocuments found hidden in desk drawer
OL,6,FMr Rodger, a business consultant,
OL,7,Fsaid: "The papers add to a fascinating
OL,8,Fcollection of letters maps and photos,
OL,9,Ftelling the story of the 8th Army's
OL,10,Fadvance through North Africa, Italy,
OL,11,Fand into Austria in the last three
OL,12,Fyears of the war, defeat of the
OL,13,FGermans turning into the race for
OL,14,FBerlin which shaped Western Europe for
OL,15,Fthe next 50 years.
OL,17,F"The perspective of a signals officer,
OL,18,Fconstantly on the move, keeping troops
OL,19,Fconnected to their command, offers an
OL,20,Famazing overview of the conflict.
OL,26,@oD@GOUyD@AOU
