OL,3,CMan reunited with father's wartime
OL,4,Cdocuments found hidden in desk drawer
OL,6,F"There isn't much mention of the human
OL,7,Fcost of the war, and my father never
OL,8,Freally spoke of this, perhaps
OL,9,Ftypically.
OL,11,F"But it's a proud and detailed account
OL,12,Fof an extraordinary endeavour, told by
OL,13,Fa young man who, with the benefit of
OL,14,Fhindsight, survived and could be said
OL,15,Fto have had a 'good war'.
OL,17,FMr Reid said he is delighted to have
OL,18,Fbeen able to reunite Mr Rodger with
OL,19,Fhis father's papers.
